{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Grease a silicone mold with non-stick cooking spray.","Place a bowl onto mixing bowl lid and weigh in 4 oz fruit juice. Add gelatin, whisk to combine and set aside to absorb juice and soften.","Place 12 oz fruit juice, sugar and citric acid into mixing bowl and cook <nobr>4 min\/170°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Add reserved gelatin mixture and mix <nobr>2 min\/speed 2<\/nobr>. Transfer into prepared mold and refrigerate until set (approx. 1 hr.).","Unmold gummies and place on parchment to dry. Let set for one day. Store in an airtight container until ready to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["non-stick cooking spray","16 oz fruit juice, divided","6 packets\/envelopes gelatin powder","2 ½ oz sugar","½ tsp citric acid (see Tip)"]}],"id":"r411303","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-eWydxtTiKx8\/XZWe_ZHhtyI\/AAAAAAAAe88\/xi2fEZgxJZIgpGUG73BPYHlXEU2ja8qrwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_lWf3auKvpGvDYxwc.png","title":"Fruit Juice Gummies","publishedAt":"2018-10-19T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"0 g","fat":"0 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"1 g","calories":"8 kJ \/ 2 kcal"},"usefulItems":"wire whisk, parchment paper, silicone gummy bear mold, airtight container, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["Quantity of gummies may vary depending on size of mold.","Citric acid can be purchased in health food stores or where canning supplies are sold.","Try different fruit juices for different flavors and colors e.g., apple, pomegranate, orange and mixed berry juice or even store-bought fruit juice smoothies."],"basicInfo":["medium","25m","25h 25m","265 pieces"]}